@startuml
title Request and Interpret Environmental Data

actor "Public User /\nThird-Party Developer" as Client
participant "Functional Client\n(Digital Signage)" as FC
participant "Provide\nPublic API" as API
participant "Data Distribution\nManagement" as DDM
database "Analytics\nDB" as DB

Client -> FC : Open SCEMAS Display
FC -> API : GET /api/v1/zones/aqi
API -> API : Rate Limit Check

group Rate Limit Passed
    API -> DDM : Request Aggregated Data
    DDM -> DB : Query Latest Aggregates
    DB --> DDM : Aggregated Zone Metrics
    DDM -> DDM : Compute AQI per Zone
    DDM -> DDM : Strip Sensitive Fields\n(sensor IDs, device metadata)
    DDM --> API : ZoneAQI[]
    API --> FC : 200 OK + JSON Payload
    FC --> Client : Display Zone AQI Cards
end

group Rate Limit Exceeded
    API --> FC : 429 Too Many Requests
    FC --> Client : Display Error Message
end

note over API,DB
  same aggregate-only flow also backs:
  - GET /api/v1/zones/summary
  - GET /api/v1/zones/{zoneId}/current
  - GET /api/v1/zones/{zoneId}/history
  - GET /api/v1/rankings
  - GET /api/v1/metrics
  - GET /api/v1/status
end note

@enduml
